Decision summary
- Made In England is the better fit because it most directly satisfies the highest‑priority items in my self‑introduction: warm mid‑era analog tone, spacious/preserved dynamics, intimate and clearly placed lead vocals, subtle multi‑part harmonies and cohesive sequencing that reward start‑to‑finish listening. These specific attributes outweigh the attractive single‑forward qualities of Somewhere Over the Rainbow, which—despite preserving dynamics and offering tasteful country elements—reads as more single‑anchored and lacks the explicit warm mid‑era sheen, layered harmonies, and album‑focused presentation that I currently favor.

